# gen198 — RATCHETED (was gen192's open gap). F5 verification by RUNNING: the rung
# past run_verify ("it links") to "it ran and did X". A "build and run <path>" cue
# compiles+links the file into a temp executable, EXECUTES it in a sandboxed child,
# and reports the program's REAL exit status read from the process — the grounded
# oracle the swe-bench loop needs ("did the test pass?"), not a guess (CODE-MASTERY
# §4). The compiler+process is a deterministic tool, not outsourced intelligence.
#expect: pass
#faculty: run-execute
# A program that exits 0.
> build and run tests/code/buildable/prog.c and tell me its exit code
< it ran and exited with code 0.
# A program that exits NON-zero: the verdict is the real code (7), not a constant.
> build and run tests/code/buildable/exit7.c and tell me its exit code
< it ran and exited with code 7.